

	 
      He who closes his eyes sees nothing, even in the full light of day.   If you're not living on the edge you're taking up too much space.   Given enough time  resources, good security testing will ultimately penetrate the system. The role of the system designer is to make penetration cost more than the value of information that will be obtained.   The problem is not that there are problems. The problem is expecting otherwise  thinkin that having problems is a problem. 
     

    
